        <investigation>
            <p>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                What is the FOIL method, and why is it useful for multiplying binomials?
            </p>
        </investigation>

        <p>
            Suppose we want to Multiply
            <me>
                (a + b)(c +d)
            </me>
            We have;
        </p>

        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>(a + b)(c +d) \amp = (ac) + (ad) + (bc) + (bd)</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>

        <example>

            <statement>
                <p>
                    
                </p>
                <p>
                    Find the product:
                    <me>
                        (3x - 2)(5x +8)
                    </me>                
                </p>
            </statement>

            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(3x) \cdot (5x) \amp = 15x^2 </mrow>
                        <mrow>(3x) \cdot(8) \amp =  24x</mrow>
                        <mrow>(-2) \cdot (5x) \amp = -10x </mrow>
                        <mrow>(-2) \cdot (8) \amp = -16</mrow>
                    </md>
                    Now combine the terms:
                    <md>
                        <mrow>15x^2 + 24x - 10x + 16 \amp = 15x^2 + 14x - 16 </mrow>
                    </md>

                    Therefore;
                    <md>
                        <mrow> (3x - 2)(5x + 8) \amp = 15x^2 + 14x - 16</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

        <p>
            From the example we can see we formed an algrebaric expressions
        </p>
        <p>
            The product of two identical binomials is known as the square of the binomial and is written as:
            <me>
                (a + b)^2
            </me>
            <md>
                <mrow>(a + b)^2 \amp = a^2 + ab + ab + b^2</mrow>
            </md>
            <md>
                <mrow> \amp = a^2 + 2ab + b^2 </mrow>
            </md>
            Therefore;
            <me>
                (a + b)^2 = a^2 + 2ab + b^2
            </me>
            If the two terms are of the form (ax + b) and (ax - b) then their product is:
            <me>
                (a + b)(a - b)
            </me>            
            <md>
                <mrow> (a + b)(a - b) \amp = a^2 - ab + ab - b^2 </mrow>
            </md>
            Collecting terms;
            <md>
                <mrow> \amp = a^2 - b^2 </mrow>
            </md>
            Thus, the product is:
            <md>
                <mrow>(a + b)(a - b) \amp a^2 - b^2</mrow>
            </md>
            Now this is the difference of squares formula.
        </p>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    
                </p>
                <p>
                    Form a qudratic expression:
                    <me>
                        (8x + 5)^2
                    </me>                
                </p>
            </statement>

            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(8x + 5)^2 \amp = (8x + 5)(8x + 5) </mrow>
                    </md>
                    Expanding the brackets
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \amp 64x^2 + 40x + 40x + 25 </mrow>
                    </md>
                    Collect like terms and form a quadratic expressions:
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \amp 64x^2 + 80x + 25 </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

